PGObject-Util-PGConfig

This module provides some basic abstraction functions around PostgreSQL
configuration file (postgresql.conf, recovery.conf) syntax.  The module
assumes one has one of these objects per file (but it makes only the
assumption that the values provided are valid for that file.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc PGObject::Util::PGConfig

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=PGObject-Util-PGConfig

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/PGObject-Util-PGConfig

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/PGObject-Util-PGConfig

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/PGObject-Util-PGConfig/


